<DOCNO> NYT19990624.0049 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 02:45 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7702 &Cx1f; tth-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-FINALS-SPI &LR;      06-24 0945
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-FINALS-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TWIN TOWERS POINT SPURS TOWARD NBA TITLE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By RONALD TILLERY  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ All you need to know about Wednesday night is movie
director and Knicks maniac Spike Lee's mouth seemed wired shut. He
was too unflappable in his courtside seat.
</P>
<P>
   Bad news if you are Knicks fan.
</P>
<P>
   The envelope for best team in the 1999 NBA season is close to
being opened, and the Knicks suddenly seem like Lee at the Oscars:
Waiting to applaud the original favorite who eventually won.
</P>
<P>
   That is the case following San Antonio's 96-89 Game 4 victory
against the Knicks at Madison Square Garden. The Spurs lead the
best-of-seven NBA Finals 3-1, and are just one win from winning
their first championship.
</P>
<P>
   San Antonio can also become the first former ABA team to win a
title with a win here Friday in Game 5. No team has ever recovered
from a 3-1 deficit in the Finals.
</P>
<P>
   After shaking off a Game 3 defeat, the Spurs are well aware of
Finals history.
</P>
<P>
   ``We definitely don't want to give them any opportunity for
life. ... It's a one-game thing,'' Spurs center Tim Duncan said.
``We just want to knock them out.''
</P>
<P>
   This series has been about the Knicks' difficulty in climbing
the deeper Spurs and their two 7-footers. It was the same story
Wednesday for New York, which got pummeled inside by the Spurs'
Duncan and David Robinson.
</P>
<P>
   They combined for 42 points, 35 rebounds and 7 blocked shots.
Duncan and Robinson shut down the lane in the final five minutes,
making the Knicks' fourth-quarter comeback attempt a feeble one.
</P>
<P>
   ``Size does matter in this league,'' Knicks coach Jeff Van Gundy
said. ``It does. And particularly in the playoffs. And their size
beat our speed and quickness because not only did they affect us on
the boards and the post scoring, but every penetration was a
difficult, difficult shot.''
</P>
<P>
   There are two words that now describe the Knicks' chances:
Difficult and improbable. Though the Knicks made history by
becoming the first eighth seed to reach the Finals, they must win
Friday, and two games at San Antonio to create more.
</P>
<P>
   ``That makes it more fun,'' said Knicks center Marcus Camby, who
started for the second straight game. ``When we were 21-21, no one
gave us a shot at making the playoffs. Probably none of you guys
thought we'd be in the Finals. We're all about making history.
People doubted us before, they're going to doubt us now.''
</P>
<P>
   And with good reason if Duncan and Robinson continue to have
such a strong say.
</P>
<P>
   Combined, they outrebounded the Knicks, who at a team grabbed 34
rebounds. Robinson was the biggest force. He finished with four
blocks _ two more than New York had _ and nine offensive rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Instead of going after jump shots, ``we made them come into the
paint,'' Robinson said. ``We challenged their layups, their dunks.
It's great when you make a block (and) convert on the other end.''
</P>
<P>
   Duncan said he could see the Knicks wilt.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was kind of heartbreaking for them every time (Robinson)
was able to tip one in,'' Duncan said.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've been talking about it the whole series. We know they go
to the offensive boards hard and we know we have some studs to get
to our offensive boards.''
</P>
<P>
   New York, though, never gave up.
</P>
<P>
   The Knicks fought back from a 13-point deficit in the second
half. They could have tied the score or taken a lead twice with
five minutes left in the game.
</P>
<P>
   But each time, the Spurs got big baskets from Duncan or
Robinson. It was a Robinson jumper followed by Duncan's hook shot
that extended the Spurs' 81-80 advantage.
</P>
<P>
   Ahead 86-84, Mario Elie and Robinson each made two free throws.
Sean Elliott's pair of free throws with 57.6 seconds left put the
Spurs ahead 92-84 and iced the victory.
</P>
<P>
   New York's Allan Houston _ the hero in Game 3 _ did not have a
basket in the final five minutes.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just missed some shots,'' Houston said. ``I wasn't
frustrated. I wasn't tired. I had some good looks. I made those
shots most the time I took them.''
</P>
<P>
   The Knicks' last lead was 39-38 with six minutes left in the
second. San Antonio took a 50-46 lead into halftime and distanced
itself at the start of the third with a 9-0 run.
</P>
<P>
   The Spurs' 72-63 advantage, which they took into the fourth
quarter, was their biggest of the game.
</P>
<P>
   Houston and Camby each scored 20 points. Sprewell had 26. But
the Spurs finished with better scoring balance. All five San
Antonio starters scored 14 points or more.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps none were bigger than Avery Johnson's 14 points and 10
assists.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's the guy who makes us feel like we've got coordination on
every possession. He's the man for us,'' Spurs coach Gregg Popovich
said of Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   Both teams shot the ball well and played to their strengths
early. The Knicks ran up and down the floor, scoring off
fastbreaks. San Antonio re-established its inside game with Duncan
and Robinson overpowering whomever New York put in front of them.
</P>
<P>
   Part of that had to do with the emergence of the point guards.
</P>
<P>
   The Knicks' Charlie Ward was effective early, igniting
fastbreaks and finding teammates for easy baskets. Johnson
countered when he got his running left-handed hook shot to fall in
the first quarter. He also set up Duncan and Robinson deep in the
post.
</P>
<P>
   ``You've got to break down their defense,'' Johnson said.
``Sometimes I gave into (the Knicks') pressure. I wanted to be a
little more aggressive and if I didn't score that meant we were
going to get offensive rebounds, and David had nine of them.''
</P>
<P>
   An important number in Game 4. Now the magic number is one.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
