<P>
   BOOK-NOTES _ Simon &AMP; Schuster will publish book this fall on the
100 Most Influential People of the Century, as selected from Time
magazine. The book will contain essays written by famous people
about famous people _ Lee Iacocca on Henry Ford, Salman Rushdie on
Gandhi, etc. Also, J.D. Salinger's problems continue. In the wake
of the auction of Salinger's letters to Joyce Maynard, a new book
gives detailed directions to the reclusive writer's house; Warner
plans a book tie-in to the movie ``Eyes Wide Shut,'' with the
screenplay of the film as well as the original book the script is
based on _ ``Dream Story'' by Arthur Schnitzler. (O'Briant, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) 21
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-COFFEE _ Mark Pendergrast, who was not allowed to drink
coffee when he was growing up in Buckhead, has devoted the last
four years to chronicling its history. We discussed his new book,
``Uncommon Grounds,'' over a cup of house blend at Aurora. It's
about time Americans had a taste of decent coffee; until recently,
he says, our coffee stunk.(Auchmutey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25. WITH PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   AUTHOR-SUGAR _ Sugar Rautbord, the Chicago-bred philanthropist
and Republican fund-raiser, has been keeping up a busy schedule of
book promotions since her third novel, The Chameleon, was released
in May by Warner Books. She touched down in Palm Beach, her familys
vacation home for 30 years, recently for a book-signing party
organized by her sister, Palm Beach resident Pat Tracy. (Sjostrom,
Palm Beach Daily News). WITH PHOTO. MOVED SATURDAY, JUNE 19.
</P>
