<P>
   WITH: ONLINE TRAVEL -- The founders of LastMinuteTravel.com plan
to convince travelers across the nation that the best kind of
travel is the last-minute kind, booked online. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-MAPS _ In which we consider that much-cursed,
much-consulted fact of summer vacation, the road map. Automobile
road maps first apperared with automobiles a century ago. From the
teens through the '70s, millions were printed and given away for
free. Now you have to buy them--if you don't have a computerized
one in your dashboard. We unfold the history, talk to collectors,
visit the map archives in Chicago, weave in the romance of
cartography. Yes, romance; a map is just lines on paper, but as
Jack Kerouac and others have noted, those lines can unleash some
poerful yearnings. (Auchmutey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)WITH
PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, June 27.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-TECHMAPS _ The latest thing in personal navigation is a
lot like the oldest thing: asking directions. OnStar, the General
Motors program that links a car with a navigator sitting at a
computerized map somewhere in Michigan, is like having a gas
station attendant available for questioning 24 hours a day. The
most popular paperless road maps are software programs; we checked
out Microsoft's Expedia Streets &AMP; Trips 2000.(Auchmutey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)WITH PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, June 27.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-MAPTRIPS _ All this talk about mpas makes you want to
just GO. Here are 15 driving trip ideas from ``The Most Scenic
Drives in America.''(Auchmutey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embaroged for Sunday, June 27.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-ALASKA _ RESURRECTION BAY, Alaska _ If you do only one
thing in Alaska, a Kenai Fjords Tours cruise of the Resurrection
Bay area will fill your memory with mental snapshots of glaciers,
sea otters, bald eagles, mountain goats and possibly even a giant
humpback whale. (Auchmutey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
