<P>
   FASHION-WHITE _ The pope wears it religiously. So does novelist
Tom Wolfe who penned ``A Man in Full.'' Tennis fanatics court it
everyday. Brides and debutantes also slip into it on their big day.
It's the color white, the hottest shade for warm-weather dressing
and the perfect antidote to endless seasons of black. (MJohnson,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS. 12.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed until Sunday, June 27.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-GOODWILLJEANS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Would you climb
out of your Calvins to wear a pair of bluejeans made in Miami by
Goodwill workers? Goodwill's G.I. Pride jeans, selling for the
patriotic price of $17.76, go on sale July 4 at 17 Miami-Dade
County Goodwill stores. If G.I. Pride sells well in Miami-Dade, the
jeans will be rolled out to 1,600 Goodwill stores nationally.
``We're as qualified to make a good pair of jeans as anyone else,''
says Dennis Pastrana, South Florida Goodwill Industries president.
(Lomartire, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   WILDFLOWERS _ ATHENS, Ga. _ Wilbur and Marion Duncan have done
it again. The noted botanists have penned a new book, ``Wildflowers
of the Eastern U.S.,'' an update on their first account about
plants of the Southeast. A profile of their long, rewarding career
and the garden they've built near Athens, Ga. (McCarthy, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 30. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ Growing mullein has never been easier for Lee
May. One flower stalk at last measurement had reached 7 feet,
several feet taller than any he'd grown before. Not surprising, all
who see this monster mullein can't resist comparisons to Jack's
fabled beanstalk, alien plants from sci-fi flicks. (May, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 21. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   WORKSHOP-CORNICES _ Return of the Workshop series: This week, a
how-to on homemade cornice boards. (Brooks, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
