   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BILLS-ONLINE (San Francisco) _ In another leap forward on the
electronic commerce frontier, three of the nation's strongest banks
_ Wells Fargo &AMP; Co., Chase Manhattan Corp. and First Union Corp. _
have formed a new venture to deliver electronic bills to online
consumers and businesses. By EDWARD IWATA.
</P>
<P>
   UAL-SHANGHAI (San Francisco) _ United Airlines, the biggest
carrier at San Francisco International Airport, with half of all
flights and passengers, will become the first U.S. airline to fly
nonstop between Shanghai and San Francisco, starting next spring.
By DAVID ARMSTRONG.
</P>
<P>
   HOME-PRICES (San Francisco) _ The median price for a Bay Area
home has passed a new milestone: $300,000. The next closest area in
California was Orange County, where people paid a median price of
$262,000. The median price for the state was $181,000 last month.
By VICTORIA COLLIVER.
</P>
