</P>
<P>
   COMPUTER-RETRAINING (Albany, N.Y.) _ In antiseptic,
air-conditioned computer training classrooms, humming with the
white noise of pentium processors, a quiet revolution is taking
place in this regin. People in their 40s and 50s have become the
students (``career changers'') and technological whiz kids in their
20s and 30s are their teachers (``trainers''). The trend has been
fueled by the fallout of downsizing and plant closings as well as a
workplace increasingly reliant on workers with computer expertise.
By PAUL GRONDAHL.
</P>
