</P>
<P>
   X-GAMES-HAWK (San Francisco) _ The face of the X Games is not
some prepubescent, trash- mouthed hellion with a pierced tongue,
hair down to his waist, shorts down to his shins and a Black
Sabbath T-shirt. Rather, it's Tony Hawk, the most famous
skateboarder in the world _ the guy whom publicists and journalists
love to refer to as ``The Michael Jordan of skateboarding.'' The
made-for-TV competition begins this weekend. By MARK FAINARU-WADA.
</P>
<P>
   RUN-TRACK-FIELD (Eugene, Ore.) _ Although the USA Track &AMP; Field
Championships involve 39 men's and women's events contested over
four days, the meet can be condensed to a single 20-second flash of
pure sex appeal: Michael Johnson vs. Maurice Greene in the 200
meters on Sunday. By JOHN CRUMPACKER.
</P>
