<TEXT>
<P>
   Put that car in drive and see america's scenic vistas
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, June 27.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Auchmutey
</P>
<P>
   All this talk about maps makes you want to just GO. Here are
some ideas from ``The Most Scenic Drives in America'' (Reader's
Digest, $30):
</P>
<P>
   1. Columbia River Road. Washington 14 from Portland to The
Dalles. 140 miles. Along the majestic gorge Lewis and Clark
traveled.
</P>
<P>
   2. Big Sur. California 1 from San Luis Obispo to Monterey. 125
miles. The cliffs, the waves, Hearst Castle _ perhaps the
continent's most dramatic drive.
</P>
<P>
   3. Beartooth Country. U.S. 212 from Yellowstone National Park to
Red Lodge, Mont., and beyond. 120 miles. One of the highest roads
anywhere, crossing the Beartooth Pass at 10,947 feet above sea
level. You'll see snow banks in June.
</P>
<P>
   4. Colorado Springs Loop. 220-mile circuit on several roads,
past Pikes Peak and the Cripple Creek mining camps.
</P>
<P>
   5. Texas Hill Country. 310-mile wandering route from San Antonio
to Austin that takes in the limestone bluffs and bluebonnet meadows
at the heart of the state.
</P>
<P>
   6. Ozarks. Arkansas 7 from Hot Springs to Harrison, U.S. 62 to
Eureka Springs. 200 miles. White water and magnificent rock
formations, ending in one of the prettiest Victorian towns
imaginable.
</P>
<P>
   7. Upper Peninsula Drive. From the Wisconsin-Michigan border to
Mackinac Bridge. 395 miles. The serene north woods in between two
of the Great Lakes.
</P>
<P>
   8. Heart of Kentucky. 270 miles. Bowling Green to Lexington,
from cave country to the lush pastures and white-rail fences of the
bluegrass region.
</P>
<P>
   9. Lookout Mountain Parkway. Gadsden, Ala., to Chattanooga along
several routes.120 miles. We've all seen the head of the mountain
in Tennessee, but how many of us have driven its 80-mile spine?
</P>
<P>
   10. Overseas Highway. U.S. 1 from Key Largo to Key West, Fla.
127 miles. Like sailing away. Sunset is the best time.
</P>
<P>
   11. Blue Ridge Parkway. Waynesville, N.C. to Waynesboro, Va. 469
miles. The low speed limit and lack of commercial vehicles make
this one of the greatest mountain drives.
</P>
<P>
   12. Outer Banks. Kitty Hawk to Nags Head to Ocracoke, N.C. 115
miles. The Wright Brothers, Cape Hatteras, miles of sand dunes.
</P>
<P>
   13. Pennsylvania Dutch Country. 80-mile swing through the
beautiful Amish farmlands around Lancaster. Intercourse,
Bird-in-Hand, Paradise _ where did they get these town names?
</P>
<P>
   14. Hudson River Valley. From the George Washington Bridge to
Hyde Park, N.Y. 75 miles. The mighty Hudson looks like an inland
sea as it rolls past West Point, ``Rip Van Winkle'' country, and
the mansions of Franklin D. Roosevelt and John D. Rockefeller.
</P>
<P>
   15. Maine Coast. U.S. 1 from Brunswick to Ellsworth, with
several detours down peninsulas. 300 miles. Lobsters, lighthouses,
miles of craggy shoreline.
</P>
<P>
   _ Jim Auchmutey writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
