 ART ADV.: Photos with WORKING-LESS and LAW-FAMILY are being
transmitted to NYT Photo Service subscribers.  
 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CANADA-PIGS (Montreal) _ In a biotech breakthrough, Canadian
scientists have created a pig whose manure is expected to do far
less harm to the environment than ordinary porkers. By Colin
Nickerson. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   PORN-PRIVACY (Boston) _ Since it was learned the executive
director of a homeless shelter has quit because of internet
pornography, a debate has developed about whether an employee's
personal computer is anyone's business. By James Bandler. 800
words.
</P>
<P>
   FIGHTING-IRISH (Boston) _ Now that Massachusetts in Ireland week
has arrived, Boston College is grousing that UMass is trying to
upstage it as the prime link between Ireland and the largest Irish
community outside the Emerald Isle. Most of the UMass delegation
are BC grads, and the spokesmen for either university are cousins,
making the sting of it all that much worse. By Kate Zernike. 1100
words.
</P>
<P>
   EPILEPSY-TREATMENT (Undated) _ Scientists studying unique brain
waves say they may have found a better way to help epileptics. by
Karen Hsu. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   JACOBY-COLUMN (Undated) _ What do American Muslims have to say
about the ominous roundup of Jews in Iran? Not much. By Jeff
Jacoby.
</P>
<P>
   ELLIS-COLUMN (Undated) -- ``You can't beat something with
nothing'' applies even when that something is as cynical as
Democratic posturing on ``gun control.'' By John Ellis.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LIFESTYLE &LR;   &UR; (l) &LR;
