   w/
</P>
<P>
   LAW-FAMILY (Undated) _ Law firms make special demands on their
employees, a particularly difficult proposition for lawyers with
families. By Steve Wilmsen. 900 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   CHILDCARE-COLUMN (Undated) _ If you're a parent getting ready to
send your kids to visit their father or mother for part of the
summer, give yourself a break. By Barbara Meltz. (Last of a
two-part series.) 1675 words.
</P>
<P>
   FAMILY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Invented ritual fills a need. By Linda
Weltner.
</P>
<P>
   HANDYMAN-HOTTON (Undated) _ Stubborn casement may need new arm.
By Peter Hotton.
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-LYME (Undated) -- Deer ticks pose a serious Lyme disease
threat, so protection needed in summer. By Ruth Foster.
</P>
<P>
   WHITE-COLUMN (Undated) _ Dee Dee hesitates to take on the word
``shag.'' However her hotline has been ringing with calls from
anxious citizens confused by the term. By Diane White.
</P>
