<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EDITOR-APPOINT-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KATHERINE BETTS NAMED EDITOR OF HARPER'S BAZAAR MAGAZINE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Katherine (Kate) Betts, 35, former fashion news
director of Vogue magazine, has been appointed editor-in-chief of
Harper's BAZAAR magazine, Cathleen P. Black, president of Hearst
Magazines, announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Betts, who succeeds the late Elizabeth (Liz) Tilberis, will join
the company immediately. Her first full issue will be the December
issue that will appear on newsstands in mid-November.
</P>
<P>
   ``Kate's reputation in the fashion magazine industry is
extraordinary _ both here in the U.S. and in Europe,'' said Black.
``She has been an innovator in covering fashion beyond the design
world and on the runway. Her view extends into the home, into arts
and entertainment, and every other aspect of our 21st century
lifestyles.''
</P>
<P>
   In a statement, Betts said she wants to make Harper's BAZZAR
``the style source for readers'' by adding to the mix of fashion,
design and photography that characterize the magazine.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to offer readers the best service pages in the
business,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Betts has worked at Vogue since 1991, most recently as fashion
news director. She was responsible for developing and producing all
fashion features including runway reports, designer profiles, and
popular culture stories. Betts was editor of such sections as
``Vogue's View'' and ``Vogue's Index,'' a special shopping section
which she created in 1995, and the magazine's supplements.
</P>
<P>
   Before joining Vogue, Betts was a reporter for, and later the
bureau chief of, the Paris office of Fairchild Publications from
1988 to 1991. While managing the Paris office of the daily trade
newspaper WWD, W and M magazines, she helped launch W Europe. She
also has worked for Metropolitan Home, the International Herald
Tribune and European Travel &AMP; Life.
</P>
<P>
   She is a graduate of Princeton University.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-24-99 1455EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
