<HEADER>
A8351 &Cx1f; taf-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ALBUM-OF-THE-WEEK-NYT     06-24 0307
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ALBUM-OF-THE-WEEK-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SPOTLIGHT ON A NEW ALBUM 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 By NEIL STRAUSS   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MISSY MISDEMEANOR ELLIOTT: ``Da Real World'' (Gold
Mind/EastWest), and THE CHEMICAL BROTHERS: ``Surrender''
(Astralwerks). Two of the finest party albums of 1997 were Ms.
Elliott's future-minded rap and rhythm-and-blues debut, ``Supa Dupa
Fly,'' and the Chemical Brothers' big-beat electronic rump-shaker,
``Dig Your Own Hole.''
</P>
<P>
   But the party has ended for both of these acts: in the
intervening years, their style has been widely imitated and, partly
in response, both have forced themselves forward, darkening and
mellowing their sound, indulging in many (perhaps too many)
collaborations and, in the case of the Chemical Brothers, sampling
Ms. Elliott's music.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Elliott, one of the most successful black female producers
and songwriters, focuses on reclamation here: not just in trying
(half-successfully) to put a positive spin on disrespectful female
slurs but also in being an aggressor, with males as victim.
</P>
<P>
   Produced with Timbaland, the songs are full of minor-key string
samples, ominous rapping and staggered, stuttering beats. But the
rapping, the collaborations (particularly with Eminem) and the
arrangements are uneven, resulting in a pretty good album that one
often wants to be better than pretty good.
</P>
<P>
   The third Chemical Brothers album comes on strong with the
robotic bleep-and-grind of ``Music: Response,'' which samples an
Elliott-Timbaland production, before detouring into new wave (with
Bernard Sumner of New Order), Beatles psychedelia (featuring,
predictably, Noel Gallagher of Oasis) and ambient drone (with Mazzy
Star).
</P>
<P>
   Though fans expecting this pair of English DJs to kickstart a
party with ``Surrender'' may be disappointed, those expecting a
varied mix tape won't be. -
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
