<P>
   FILM-BIG DADDY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ In ``Big Daddy,'' Adam Sandler shows a kind of ...
well, I'm not sure maturity is the word I'm looking for, but there
is an evolution here. This movie will make a kind of history all
the same _ the moment when the title ``Big Daddy'' came to suit
Sandler's status in the entertainment world. By ELVIS MITCHELL.
Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-IDEAL HUSBAND &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``An Ideal Husband'' is a handsomely mounted
adaptation of playwright Oscar Wilde's look at the intrigues of
longing. Instead of looking like a big-screen antique catalog,
where you'd love buying the rooms but you can't imagine anybody
living in them, ``Husband'' is stocked with people you can relate
to. By ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-SEXUAL INNOCENCE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ In Mike Figgis' newest film, the convoluted and
pretentious puzzle ``The Loss of Sexual Innocence,'' those who
don't get up and walk out may be too hypnotized by the imagery. And
you can tell that all this tony, film-school philosophizing means
something to Figgis _ he's not just showing off. By ELVIS MITCHELL.
Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
