   BIZBOOKS-REVIEWS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Remember how easy it was for business during the Cold
War? Not that it was pleasant living with a nuclear arsenal pointed
at us all the time, but, back then, the American and the Soviet
governments were more or less in charge of most everything. Then,
the Berlin wall came down in 1989. And everything changed. Welcome
to globalization. A new book, artfully written by New York Times
foreign affairs columnist Thomas Friedman, provides an insightful
look at the chaotic world in which we now live, a world in which
global business is the dominant mover and shaker. By TERESA MCUSIC.
Story will move in ``f'' financial category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
