<P>
   COXNET NASCAR PAGE
</P>
<P>
   COXNET NASCAR 0624 _Jimmy Spencer has watched his NASCAR season
literally go up in smoke. A year ago, Spencer, 42, of Berwick, Pa.,
was ninth in the points standings heading into Sears Point Raceway,
the first of two road-course events on the Winston Cup circuit.
When the Winston Cup series makes its annual stop in the San
Francisco area on Sunday, however, Spencer will find himself 29th
in points, trailing leader Dale Jarrett by a whopping 1,056.
Spencer's main problem has been blown engines, and his sponsor,
Winston cigarettes, says it won't be back next season. However,
Jimmy Spencer says last week's top five finish has rejuvenated his
campaign. (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 15-18''
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR-NOTES _ Notes column. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
