   OLYSPECIAL _ RALEIGH _ After years of preparation, North
Carolina is bracing today (Friday) for the beginning of what is
being touted as this year's largest multi-sport athletic event in
the world. The 10th Special Olympics World Summer Games will be
held in Raleigh, Durham, Chapel Hill and Cary beginning Saturday
through July 4. Many of the 7,000 athletes and 2,000 coaches from
150 countries and territories have spent the week training and
being entertained in 150 towns and cities across North Carolina,
but today they are converging on Raleigh, Durham and Chapel Hill
along with 15,000 family members and more than 35,000 volunteers.
(Chamberlain, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
