   KOSOVO-MARINES (Zegra, Yugoslavia) _ If the U.S. marines who
have taken over this remote part of southeastern Kosovo came to
forge peace between Kosovo's Serbs and Albanians, the result was
anything but. The firefight that killed one Serb and wounded two
others on Wednesday night sank Zegra, like so many other villages
across Kosovo, into a new contortion of fear, violence and
retribution. By Steven Lee Myers.
</P>
