<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-REFLECT (Washington) _ The heated accusations of
monopoly, the lively e-mail flavored with capitalist aggression and
the emphatic testimony alleging and denying misconduct came to a
close Thursday as the last witness stepped off the stand in
Microsoft antitrust trial, eight months after proceedings began.
The Microsoft trial is by no means over, but it sharply shifts
gears as the daily theater in the courtroom gives way to a more
sober weighing of facts and law. By Steve Lohr. &QL;
</P>
