  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
June 25 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Eddie Ibardolasa at (818) 713-3602. 
 
 
BBN-DODGERS-PADRES (Los Angeles) _ The Los Angeles Dodgers face the
San Diego Padres at 7:10 p.m. PDT. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
RAC-BUDROYALE (Inglewood, Calif.) _ Former claimer trying to win
the biggest race of his career _ sound familiar? No, the horse is
not Charismatic. He's Budroyale, a 6-year-old who's hoping to
capture the magic of Charismatic in this Sunday's Hollywood Gold
Cup. 
By Kevin Modesti. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
GEN-LEGISLATION (Los Angeles) _ Story on a bill making its way
through the state legislature that prevent a repeat of the Cal
State Northridge fiasco two years ago. Authored by Sen. Cathie
Wright (R-Simi Valley), the bill would prohibit universities and
junior colleges from cutting any sports programs for one year after
making a decision to do so and would require public hearings on the
matter. The bill passed out of committee and is being negotiated by
lawmakers before reaching both houses. Despite opposition from the
CSU lobby, it's gaining momentum and looks as if it will pass this
session. 
By Chris Branam. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
GEN-WRIGHT (Los Angeles) _ A look at Cathie Wright. Cynics might
say Wright swooped into the CSUN debate two years ago for political
reasons (she added an amendment to the budget that year that
provided Northridge with a one-time bailout of around $100,000),
but she has steadfastly stayed on the case, working behind the
scenes to promote her bill. A huge sports fan, she really believes
in this cause. 
By Lee Barnathan. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
GEN-RUSSELL (Los Angeles) _ Feature on San Fernando Valley activist
Duke Russell, who fights to save local college and JC sports. 
By Lee Barnathan. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
