<P>
   HANFORD (Washington) _ Risks from soil and groundwater
contamination at the Hanford Nuclear Reservation are becoming more
and more apparent _ Native Americans fishing near Hanford have
developed rashes suggestive of exposure to chromium, and juvenile
salmon are threatened by large quantities of that same chemical,
according to a report released Thursday. But the solutions to the
problem are elusive, and the Department of Energy is so wedded to
conventional technology that it is failing to take advantage of
recent technological advances.
