   (NYT3) NICASIO, Calif. -- June 24, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JUNE
27 -- HAUNTING-FILM, 6-24 -- Gary Rydstrom at Skywalker Ranch in
Northern California, where he is working on scary sounds for ``The
Haunting,'' set to open July 23. The film, directed by Jan De Bont,
is layered with the sounds of inhuman conversations - between wood
and air, between stone and glass, and between an evil entity and
its tormented victims. ``To me, a scary sound is one that you can't
pin down, or one that is behind you,'' says Rydstrom. (Peter
DaSilva/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- June 24, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JUNE 27 --
SEX-THEATER-2, 6-24 -- Sigourney Weaver and Guy Boyd in Christopher
Durang's ``Sex and Longing.'' One of the few American sex comedies
offered this season, its main character is a nymphomaniac who needs
sex every 15 minutes. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) NEW YORK -- June 24, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JUNE 27 --
SEX-THEATER-1, 6-24 -- Ciaran Hinds and Anna Friel in Patrick
Marber's ``Closer.'' In a culture in which sex looms as a major
presence in everything from music videos to painting, from novels
to advertising, Marber's production is one of the few offering
explorations of sex in what has been widely hailed as Broadway's
season of the play. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
