SUMMIT _ The San Francisco Chronicle has learned that federal
antitrust investigators are on the verge of approving a
controversial East Bay hospital merger, leaving it up to state
officials to decide whether to oppose the deal alone. The federal
decision will disappoint those who fear that the merger of
Oakland's Summit Medical Center with Berkeley's Alta Bates Medical
Center would less competition and higher prices for medical care.
It will also put added pressure on state Attorney General Bill
Lockyer to either oppose or amend the controversial deal.
